.TH "spi_nor_write_16bit_cr_and_check" 9 "spi_nor_write_16bit_cr_and_check" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
spi_nor_write_16bit_cr_and_check \- Write the Status Register 1 and the Configuration Register in one shot. Ensure that the byte written in the Configuration Register match the received value, and that the 16-bit Write did not affect what was already in the Status Register 1.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" spi_nor_write_16bit_cr_and_check
.BI "(struct spi_nor *nor "  ","
.BI "u8 cr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "nor" 12
pointer to a 'struct spi_nor'.
.IP "cr" 12
byte value to be written to the Configuration Register.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -errno otherwise.
